| Deathbed Confession Says Aliens Were at Roswell                    |
|   from the here-comes-the-super-copter-here-comes-the-noise-it-make|
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday July 01, @21:01 (Sci-Fi)                |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/01/1737226      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]xnuandax writes "The army's explanation of weather balloons in the
[1]Roswell, New Mexico incident 60 years ago has been dealt a serious
public relations blow. Late Army Lt. [2]Walter Haut had signed a sealed
affidavit prior to his death last year asserting that he had [3]witnessed
the wreckage of an egg-shaped craft and its extraterrestrial crew while
working at the Roswell Army Air Field. An article at News.com.au reviews
how Haut had worked as public relations officer for the Roswell base and
was involved in the original weather balloon explanation of events at the
time. This recent evidence would seem to confirm speculation that
egg-shaped saucers are notoriously difficult to fly safely at low
altitude."

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/07/01/1737226

