| Tangible Display Makes 3D Touchable                                |
|   from the haptic-happenstance dept.                               |
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday July 01, @23:07 (Displays)              |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/02/0158250      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

moon_monkey writes "Researchers in Japan have developed [0]a display that
makes 3D objects solid enough to grasp. The system, created by engineers
at Japan's NTT, combines a 3D display with a haptic glove, making 3D
items that look real but also feel solid to touch. Two cameras are used
to image an object, to make the 3D image. A computer also uses this to
render a solid representation. It could be used to inspect products
remotely, or even to shake hands with someone on the other side of the
world, the researchers say."

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/07/02/0158250

Links:
    0. http://www.newscientisttech.com/article/dn12169-tangible-display-makes-3d-images-touchable.html


