| Activation Problems in iPhone Paradise                             |
|   from the long-wait-short-celebration dept.                       |
|   posted by Zonk on Monday July 02, @01:09 (Communications)        |
|   http://apple.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/07/02/049255         |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Thomas Hawk writes "Unfortunately it appears that some activations of
Apple's new iPhone have gone badly. After waiting in line 36 hours I'm
still unable to activate my phone. I'm [1]documenting the AT&T circus
call by call on my blog. I've had my hold calls dropped, been patched
into other users unable to activate their phone instead of AT&T customer
service reps, been told that my wife must get a new phone and that the
family plan can't work for me. I've been told that the problem is that
I'm not putting a new chip into my iPhone in the slot on the left side of
my phone when no slot there exists. PR Blogger Steve Rubel has also
[2]been documenting his problems on his Twitterstream. According to an
unscientific poll being conducted by Engadget [3]about half of the people
who bought iPhones have had activation trouble with about 38% of problems
still unresolved." Even [4]the folks at MacWorld weren't immune to these
issues.

Discuss this story at:
