[0]caffiend666 writes "According to a Yahoo News story some 7-11s are
being [1]rebranded into Simpsons 'Kwik-E-Marts' . The makeover includes
fronting on the buildings that make it look like a cartoon, Simpsons
merchandise on the shelves, and Simpsons show brands available for
purchase in the store. From the article: 'The Fox/7-Eleven deal is an
example of a practice called reverse product placement. Instead of just
putting products prominently in a movie or TV show, fake goods move from
the screen to reality ... Customers have been looking at Squishees and
KrustyO's and Buzz Cola for years and have never been able to put their
hands on it.' Since the film is PG-13, no Duff beer will be available in
the stores." If you're looking for one near you, 7-11 has [2]the list of
locations on their website.

